# .pddignore.example — copy to `.pddignore` and edit for your repo.
#
#   cp .pddignore.example .pddignore
#
# Paths listed here are skipped by `pmtools status`'s PDD marker scan
# (active when storage `pdd.enabled` is true — the default). One gitignore-style
# glob per line; blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
#
# Only CANONICAL markers are actionable to begin with — the todo/inprogress
# keyword followed by `#<issue>:<estimate>` (estimate in minutes, e.g. `:60m`).
# List paths that contain marker-like text but no real puzzles, so they never
# show up as work. (This file deliberately avoids a real `#<digits>:<digits>`
# example so the scanner can't trip on its own documentation.)
#
# Glob subset: `**` matches across directories; `*` matches within one path
# segment; a pattern containing `/` is rooted at the repo top, otherwise it
# matches a basename at any depth. Negation (`!`) is not supported.

# --- dependencies / generated ---
node_modules/**

# --- test fixtures: spec files legitimately contain marker-like strings ---
tests/**/*.spec.js

# --- docs & data: prose / CSV that mentions markers without owning puzzles ---
docs/**
*.md

# --- the agent harness's own working dirs ---
.claude/**
